# Import required R libraries
library(fpp3)
us_gdp <- read.delim("US_GDP.txt", header = TRUE)
head(us_gdp)
##      YEAR    GDP    PDI    PCE PROFITS DIVIDENDS
## 1 1970 Q1 2872.8 1990.6 1800.5    44.7      24.5
## 2 1970 Q2 2860.3 2020.1 1807.5    44.4      23.9
## 3 1970 Q3 2896.6 2045.3 1824.7    44.9      23.3
## 4 1970 Q4 2873.7 2045.2 1821.2    42.1      23.1
## 5 1971 Q1 2942.9 2073.9 1849.9    48.8      23.8
## 6 1971 Q2 2947.4 2098.0 1863.5    50.7      23.7
summary(us_gdp)
##      YEAR                GDP            PDI            PCE      
##  Length:88          Min.   :2860   Min.   :1991   Min.   :1800  
##  Class :character   1st Qu.:3284   1st Qu.:2388   1st Qu.:2108  
##  Mode  :character   Median :3784   Median :2777   Median :2469  
##                     Mean   :3866   Mean   :2800   Mean   :2537  
##                     3rd Qu.:4396   3rd Qu.:3248   3rd Qu.:2959  
##                     Max.   :4903   Max.   :3548   Max.   :3281  
##     PROFITS         DIVIDENDS     
##  Min.   : 42.10   Min.   : 23.10  
##  1st Qu.: 97.62   1st Qu.: 30.57  
##  Median :134.50   Median : 62.25  
##  Mean   :131.30   Mean   : 69.16  
##  3rd Qu.:168.43   3rd Qu.:105.20  
##  Max.   :226.00   Max.   :138.50
us_gdp <- us_gdp %>%
  mutate(QUARTER = yearquarter(YEAR)) %>%
  select(-c(YEAR)) %>%
  as_tsibble(index = QUARTER)

head(us_gdp)
## # A tsibble: 6 x 6 [1Q]
##     GDP   PDI   PCE PROFITS DIVIDENDS QUARTER
##   <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>   <dbl>     <dbl>   <qtr>
## 1 2873. 1991. 1800.    44.7      24.5 1970 Q1
## 2 2860. 2020. 1808.    44.4      23.9 1970 Q2
## 3 2897. 2045. 1825.    44.9      23.3 1970 Q3
## 4 2874. 2045. 1821.    42.1      23.1 1970 Q4
## 5 2943. 2074. 1850.    48.8      23.8 1971 Q1
## 6 2947. 2098  1864.    50.7      23.7 1971 Q2
us_gdp %>% autoplot(GDP)

fit <- us_gdp %>%
  model(ARIMA(GDP))
report(fit)
## Series: GDP 
## Model: ARIMA(1,1,0) w/ drift 
## 
## Coefficients:
##          ar1  constant
##       0.3173   15.4643
## s.e.  0.1016    3.6125
## 
## sigma^2 estimated as 1174:  log likelihood=-429.95
## AIC=865.89   AICc=866.18   BIC=873.29
fit %>% forecast(h=10) %>%
  autoplot(us_gdp) +
  labs(y = "GDP", title = "US GDP")

us_gdp %>%
  ACF(GDP) %>%
  autoplot()

us_gdp %>%
  PACF(GDP) %>%
  autoplot()

us_gdp %>%
  gg_tsdisplay(plot_type="partial")
